vailable-content"><div dir=3D"auto" class=3D"body markup"><p><span>You can =
catch the first episode </span><a href=3D"https://www.robkhenderson.com/p/m=
ain-character-syndrome-keeps-getting" rel=3D"">here</a><span>. </span></p><=
p>Some topics covered here in this second installment:</p><ul><li><p><span>=
Discussing anthropologist David Gilmore=E2=80=99s fascinating insights from=
 his book </span><em>Misogyny: The Male Malady</em><span> and how it connec=
ts with the themes of the recent film </span><em>Nosferatu</em><span> (you =
can read my review of the film </span><a href=3D"https://www.robkhenderson.=
com/p/the-ideology-of-the-dangerous-female" rel=3D"">here</a><span>)</span>=
</p></li><li><p>The richer the student body, the more protests you see. Res=
earch shows the wealthier the student body, the more demonstrations. Why do=
n=E2=80=99t you see this at community colleges?</p></li><li><p><span>Though=
ts on my </span><a href=3D"https://manhattan.institute/event/troubled-conve=
rsation-with-rob-henderson-dr-drew-pinsky" rel=3D"">upcoming event</a><span=
> with Dr. Drew and what it was like to listen to his radio show =E2=80=9CL=
oveline=E2=80=9D as a kid in the early 2000s</span></p></li><li><p><span>A =
top writing coach </span><a href=3D"https://x.com/david_perell/status/18941=
43267878703562" rel=3D"">quit teaching</a><span> because ChatGPT is outperf=
orming humans on many writing-related tasks. What does this mean for the fu=
ture of writing? Personal stories and human experiences might be our best d=
efense against the rise of AI-generated content.</span></p></li><li><p>My t=
houghts on why reading long-form content stays with you longer than quick-h=
it TikToks or tweets. Why economist Tyler Cowen says charisma matters more =
in the age of AI, and how I'm applying that to my own work.</p></li><li><p>=
Academia versus journalism: why ideological conformity persists in universi=
ties but less so in journalism, despite attracting similar types of people.=
 I break down the incentives at play.</p></li><li><p>Thoughts on mentorship=
. Why helping younger people navigate their journeys can actually help you =
find clarity and satisfaction in your own life.</p></li><li><p><span>Though=
ts on Nellie Bowles' recent book, </span><em>Morning After the Revolution</=
em><span>, where she takes us inside the chaos of 2020's "defund the police=
" era in cities like Seattle and Portland. So often utopian visions often l=
ead to dystopian outcomes, especially when idealism collides with reality=
=E2=80=94something Bowles brilliantly illustrates.</span></p></li><li><p>Sh=
aring thoughts on my forthcoming essay about F. Scott Fitzgerald=E2=80=99s =
underrated short story "Babylon Revisited"=E2=80=94a reflection on the deca=
dence of the Roaring Twenties and its modern-day echoes.</p></li><li><p>I'm=
 watching the new season of White Lotus, and there=E2=80=99s an intriguing =
shift happening in how HBO depicts political divisions. More evidence of a =
vibe shift?</p></li><li><p>Why we perceive Yellowstone as conservative and =
White Lotus as liberal, despite their messages suggesting otherwise.</p></l=
i><li><p><span>What can Malaysia's experience with affirmative action teach=
 America about DEI? I share insights from Thomas Sowell=E2=80=99s global pe=
rspective in his book </span><em>Affirmative Action Around The World.</em><=
/p></li><li><p>Amy Chua=E2=80=99s idea of "market-dominant minorities" intr=
igues me=E2=80=94how resentment toward successful minorities shapes social =
policies worldwide.</p></li><li><p>My unusual adoption story. I discuss why=
 I=E2=80=99ve succeeded more than typical studies predict, and what that re=
veals about nature versus nurture.</p></li><li><p>Why I recently picked up =
a biography of Nietzsche=E2=80=94and what I=E2=80=99m hoping to discover ab=
out this profoundly misunderstood philosopher.</p></li></ul><div class=3D"p=
aywall-jump" data-component-name=3D"PaywallToDOM"></div><p>Join me for my n=
